                <Property Name="Text" >Trissa is a modification of the well known tictactoe game, where you can play in a 3D board. It has as a text interface as well as this 3D interface, in which is simpler to play.

The goal of the game is to align N balls, where N is the board&apos;s dimension. For example, if you are playing in a 5x5x5 board (you can set the dimension entering the &quot;Options&quot; menu on the first screen) you have to align 5 balls in whatever direction. Note however that not all directions inside a cube can hold N balls.

The game was though in the beginning to be used to develop algorithms to play this type of game against each other. There&apos;s a plugin mechanism that you can use to develop your algorithm. Afterwards a Human player was added using this same mechanism, so you can have some fun and also test your algorithms.

For more informations visit our site: http://github.com/lucasdemarchi/trissa/

Author:
     Lucas De Marchi
     http://www.politreco.com</Property>
